<b>RISC iX</b> was a <family wordnetid="108078020" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../815/31815.xml">
Unix-like</link></family>
 <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../194/22194.xml">
operating system</link> designed to run on the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../145/63145.xml">
Acorn Archimedes</link>. Heavily based on <O wordnetid="106832680" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../622/18932622.xml">
4.3BSD</link></O>
, it was initially completed in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../670/34670.xml">
1988</link> — a year after <O wordnetid="106832680" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../001/184001.xml">
Arthur</link></O>
 but prior to <O wordnetid="106832680" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../999/167999.xml">
RISC OS</link></O>
. Its relationship to <O wordnetid="106832680" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../593/245593.xml">
ARX</link></O>
 is unknown.
